Thanks for providing examples @pissang! 

Using coordinateSystem property sounds cleaner than parsing position values, although coordinateSystem property seems to be used in some series to position content, rather that graph itself.  Maybe positioningSystem or simply position similar to CSS?  

Another thing to think about - what if positioning attributes can be set as functions? In that case, using: 

top: function(){
   return geo.dataToPoint(latlong)
}

It would be called anytime layout changes which means no extra handlers when zoom or roam happens.. It would also allow some responsive design rules made easily. 

Going even further, if any attribute can be a function, users would be able to set color and other properties based on value which would work as an alternative to some visualMap scenarios.. 

Anyway, I'm glad this is for discussion!

